In Indonesia we have thousands report about bullying every year. Hence, please allow me to share a little bit memory of bullying here.

I got bullied years ago. It was not for only a day or a week, but it was a part of my life for couple years. I've told my parents and asked them to move me into other school after 3 years I got bullied, we tried, but it was not possible due to several reasons. So I had to keep fighting with that hell again. What I tought back in those moments was 'I will never surrender to those people who bullied me. I have to prove to them that this person could do much more better things in life than them. Because if I surrender, maybe by commit suicide, I believe that my name will be just a name and it won't give any change then I will be just a dust in the galaxy.'. People are lucky when they have parents who will got mad at those who bully their children, but my parents teached me differently, they always motivate me that it's not a big deal and I should not be too emotional. I was thinking that they would never understand what I got in school, but now I thank God and understand that it was their way to shape me into a stronger human. I never blame those people who bullied me, they were too young to understand what they did to my mental. Hey guys, I truly thank you of what you did :) For those who got bullied, please remember one thing:
"Bullying is not always a bad thing in life. If you can afford it, trust me, bullying will be a huge drive in your life. You may got bullied today, but always believe that you'll be stronger hereafter." #stopbullying #stop #bully #humanrights

caption.text:
Somewhere in the earth.
When everybody asks me "do you enjoy this job?". I will always say "I do". I don't lie because I do love this job. I feel so lucky to be placed in this segment. I achieved my dreams, to have a comfort place to learn new things. It's a very perfect world to be, to learn, to gain so many experiences I want. My working schedule is very friendly, I don't have those fears which people always told me to be prepared of before joining this company.
But, of course it would not be 100% perfect world, I obviously have some gravels on my way, here. I always be the only woman in field and people will always worried about me and say "becareful of this one and that one blablabla". Hell yeah I'm not a kid. The problem is not about the fact that I'm the only woman, but it's more likely about how men see women as a weak creature.
Entering this world in this super not right moment, when oil price is too unstable and there is always huge uncertainty, I had to be prepared of being the only one person this year to come. Somehow I'm kind of jealous with my seniors. They come together with some other people, they could talk each other and planned together about their career plan. It feels like I loose something to compete and I just do my job in a too relaxed way. But it's actually a new challenge for me to compete with myself, right? Can I beat this lazy girl inside?
